        <hl1>Silence at the Movies</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Stanley E Ely letter comments on Adam Hochschild's Oct 26 Op-Ed article opposing television sets near airport departure lounges (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Adam Hochschild (Op-Ed, Oct. 26) has a nice idea: a separate room in airports where those who want to watch television can go and leave the rest of us unbothered.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Adam Hochschild (Op-Ed, Oct. 26) has a nice idea: a separate room in airports where those who want to watch television can go and leave the rest of us unbothered.</p>
        <p>As soon as that's in place, maybe owners of movie theaters will establish eating sections, and those of us who had dinner at home can spend $8.50 and watch a film without also smelling and hearing popcorn from the next seat.</p>
        <p>STANLEY E. ELY</p>
        <p>New York, Oct. 27, 1996</p>
        <p>Seek Shelter if the Medium Is the Irritant</p>
      </block>
